docs.abstract: Judge Kavanaugh’s angry Senate testimony, urged by the White House counsel, Don McGahn, turned the tables and emboldened demoralized Republicans.
docs.snippet: Judge Kavanaugh’s angry Senate testimony, urged by the White House counsel, Don McGahn, turned the tables and emboldened demoralized Republicans.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh sat in the anteroom of Room 216 in the Hart Senate Office Building, a sterile, living-room-like space with a couch and a couple of armchairs and a large television on the wall. His chances of joining the Supreme Court seemed to be vanishing. “Disaster,” read the text message from one Republican.

headline.main: Show How You Feel, Kavanaugh Was Told, and a Nomination Was Saved
headline.print_headline: A Nomination Is Rescued by a Display of Rage and Resentment

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The woman who has accused President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee of sexual assault all but ruled out appearing at an extraordinary Senate hearing scheduled for next week to hear her allegations, insisting on Tuesday that the F.B.I. investigate first.

docs.abstract: Just 14 percent of top House staff members are nonwhite, a new study shows — a far smaller figure than in the United States as a whole or among House lawmakers.
docs.snippet: Just 14 percent of top House staff members are nonwhite, a new study shows — a far smaller figure than in the United States as a whole or among House lawmakers.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House aides write federal policy and multitrillion-dollar budgets, oversee the administration of government and shape the public’s view of Congress, but the top staff members of the House of Representatives are far less racially diverse than the country itself — or even the lawmakers who employ them.

headline.main: In an Increasingly Diverse House, Aides Remain Remarkably White
headline.print_headline: In the Hallways of Congress, a Lot of White Faces

headline.main: Grassley Refers Avenatti and a Kavanaugh Accuser for Criminal Investigation

docs.abstract: The United States government was dealt a severe setback in its decade-long attempt to prosecute private soldiers for their role in a deadly attack on unarmed Iraqis.
docs.snippet: The United States government was dealt a severe setback in its decade-long attempt to prosecute private soldiers for their role in a deadly attack on unarmed Iraqis.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States government’s decade-long attempt to prosecute four Blackwater contractors in the shooting of dozens of unarmed Iraqis in 2007, a case that became a symbol of American power run amok during the Iraq war, was dealt a blow on Wednesday when the retrial of one security guard ended in a hung jury.

headline.main: Case Against Former Blackwater Contractor Ends in Mistrial
headline.print_headline: Trial Ends in Hung Jury  For Blackwater Guard

docs.abstract: Only one North Korean was named in a complaint, but it described a team of hackers for the North’s main intelligence agency who caused hundreds of millions of dollars of damage to the global economy.
docs.snippet: Only one North Korean was named in a complaint, but it described a team of hackers for the North’s main intelligence agency who caused hundreds of millions of dollars of damage to the global economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — North Korea engaged in a yearslong effort to hack into American companies and steal from financial institutions around the globe, the Justice Department charged on Thursday in a 174-page criminal complaint that detailed how hackers caused hundreds of millions of dollars’ worth of damage to the global economy.

headline.main: U.S. Accuses North Korea of Plot to Hurt Economy as Spy Is Charged in Sony Hack
headline.print_headline: U.S. Alleges Economic Attack, Charging North Korean Hacker

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The chairman of the Senate Judiciary Committee, under mounting pressure from senators of his own party, will call President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee, Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh, and the woman who has accused him of sexual assault before the committee on Monday for extraordinary public hearings only weeks before the midterm elections.

headline.main: Hearing Set for Monday to Hear Kavanaugh and His Accuser
headline.print_headline: Court Pick and Accuser Set for Public Hearings On Sex Assault Claim
